        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=TopicQuote&amp;TOPIC_ID=4801&amp;FORUM_ID=2&amp;CAT_ID=1&amp;Forum_Title=General+Discussions&amp;Topic_Title=sun+revs+in+the+grey"><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana" size="2"> Well, glory be.  I just realised these were re-tagged as undead, finally.  Dunno how long this as been the case.  With the pet exp changes, these are an excellent source of exp at 60.  Even though they are not exactly light hitters, with shackle of spirit, you can effectivly let your pet tank these while you heal your pet up.  They are not super fast kills but give roughly twice the exp of a normal mob in the zone.  You also never run out, pretty much.  I can only take 4-5 of the 6 before they start to repop, right now.  Not only that but they are uncontested and even if they were, they are a definable camp so you can 'call' the sun revs and have a never ending supply of mobs to kill that you can easily single pull and won't find yourself clearing out lblues to try to get more darks to pop or sit arround waiting for crap to pop.</P><P>Even though they are luclin undead, they don't seem to be 100% poison resistant.  The real downside to these guys is that I can't get ignite bones to reliably stick even with scent of terris on.  That handicaps those of us with velk bracers.  Still, slightly over 100 rev kills will get you one AA point.  That's pretty speedy in my book.  It's really a 59-60 camp though.  I don't think the monk pet would hold up too well.  I have not tried fear kiting them yet but they have so much health that you'd most likely just pick up some adds.  Not even sure I can fear them as they are level 55.  They seem too resistant and have too much health for efficient root dotting.</P><P>This just struck me as a really nice untapped source of quiet, steady solo exp.</P><P><A href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=26159">Reegor</A> Mortees<BR>scaled Warlock</font></td>

